# CODEOWNERS — controls who must review PRs touching each area
# Replace @yourusername with your actual GitHub handle.
# Docs: https://docs.github.com/en/repositories/managing-your-repositorys-settings-and-features/customizing-your-repository/about-code-owners

# Default: maintainer reviews everything
*                           @SID-SURANGE

# Rules layer — conservative, maintainer-only
rules/                      @SID-SURANGE

# Core skills — maintainer-only (promoted from community)
skills/core/                @SID-SURANGE

# Install scripts — run on contributor machines, high trust
install.sh                  @SID-SURANGE
install.ps1                 @SID-SURANGE
bootstrap-project.sh        @SID-SURANGE

# Hooks — shell execution, high trust
hooks/                      @SID-SURANGE
hooks.json                  @SID-SURANGE

# Governance files
LICENSE                     @SID-SURANGE
CODEOWNERS                  @SID-SURANGE
CONTRIBUTING.md             @SID-SURANGE

# Community skills — covered by the `*` wildcard above (maintainer reviews all PRs).
# Uncomment the line below only if you want to assign a different reviewer for community skill PRs.
# skills/community/         @community-reviewer
